main event: A UFO sighting was reported by a Pan Am Airlines flight crew over Key West, Florida in 1954.
interesting points: The object was seen from the aircraft, but no detailed description of the object was provided.
The object came into view suddenly and was observed for a brief period of time.
Weather conditions were recorded, including wind speeds at different altitudes.
The report was sent from the Commander of the Maxwell Flight Service Center at Maxwell AFB in Alabama.
The report was distributed to various military commands, including the Air Defense Command, Air Technical Intelligence Center, and Headquarters USAF.
